<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12149f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12149f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12149f"> 149(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> church fair / hairshirts / whips</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A l&apos;entr&eacute;e dans la ville ou le village, ils d&eacute;couvraient leurs &eacute;paules et se fouettaient &agrave; coups redoubl&eacute;s avec une dure discipline de cordes. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Ils chantaient en se frappant de m&acirc;les cantiques, compos&eacute;s par le ma&icirc;tre, en l&apos;honneur de la Passion du Fils de Dieu. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> A Toulouse surtout, des disciplinants nouveaux se joignaient sans cesse aux anciens. Il se tint dans la ville des march&eacute;s de haires et de fouets. <br><font color="green">[Coming into towns or villages, they uncovered their shoulders and beat themselves with redoubled blows with hard whips. &hellip; Lashing themselves they sang grave canticles, composed by the master, in honour of the Passion of the Son of God. &hellip; In Toulouse especially, new penitents joined them all the time. In the town there were markets selling hairshirts and whips.]</font> <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 185 [Saint Vincent goes around with his group of around 200 flagellants]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12154e" href="c12all.htm#c12154e">VI.C.12:154(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
